-- Bank stocks rise on G20 hopes
-- 
-- Thu Apr 2, 2009 9:01am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/04/02/us-markets-stocks-beforethebell-sb-idUSTRE53134E20090402

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The Select Sector SPDR Financial ETF rose 4.2 percent on the hope that G20 meeting in London could find ways to temper the current global economic crisis. 

 Bank profits, especially of large U.S. financial institutions, are closely linked to the strength of the global economy. (Reporting by  Ryan Vlastelica ; Editing by Theodore d'Afflisio)